Four men have been charged following the theft of Ford Transit motorhomes in Surrey and Hampshire.John Lehane, 51, from West Byfleet, Surrey, was remanded in custody at Guildford Magistrates' Court on Saturday and will next appear at Lewes Crown Court on 28 June.John Doe, 45, and Cornelius Buckley, 34, both from Woking, Surrey, and Joseph Wickens, 41, from Hailsham, East Sussex, are due before Guildford Magistrates on 16 July.All four are charged with conspiracy to commit theft of a motor vehicle.
